
    == PLEASE READ THIS INFORMATION BEFORE BROWSING DROP RATES OR ASKING QUESTIONS ==
    == PLEASE READ THIS INFORMATION BEFORE BROWSING DROP RATES OR ASKING QUESTIONS ==
    == PLEASE READ THIS INFORMATION BEFORE BROWSING DROP RATES OR ASKING QUESTIONS ==


== About Drop Methods ==
Q: What is this "independent drop chance" or "random one of list"?
A: There are three styles of drop lists.
   0: "independent drop chance". Every item in one of these packs
      has a chance to individually be rolled for, and none or all of
      the items in this pack may drop.
   1: "random one of list". Every item in one of these packs has a 'weight',
      which is added to the 'weight' of every other item in the pack. The
      game then determines which single item in this pack to drop. For
      example, a pack containing items with weights '5', '10', '10' will
      have those items respectively at a 5/25, 10/25, 10/25 chance (as
      5+10+10 is 25), or 20%, 40%, 40%.
    2: "choice from list". You get to choose the item you get. Easy. 


== About Drop Tables/Drop Packs ==
Q: This chart here says that a monster has an 80% chance to drop a card,
   and a 20% chance to drop a quality card! This is obviously wrong!
A: Each monster has a loot list made up of multiple "drop packs" or "drop tables".
   *If* the drop pack is selected, then the rates shown are the chances of
   getting each item. I do not know how the server determines which drop
   packs to give loot from. A monster may drop items from multiple drop packs
   at once, and when using "independent drop chance", may drop more than one
   item from a single pack. On a line showing the monster a pack is assigned
   to, it will say "Pack 2/4". This means the monster has four drop packs
   assigned to it, and this is the second one.


== About "0.00%" ==
Q: Some things, such as Slimy Suitcase dropped by X, says 0.00%.
   Does this mean X does not drop Slimy Suitcase?
A: No. For drops from monsters, my *best guess* is that "0.00%" drop rates are 
   determined by the server. "0.00%" drop items will, usually, still drop from
   those mobs, but the rate is currently unknown (and yes, the files say '0' 
   for the rate). For gathering nodes that say "0.00%", I'm unsure if they will
   drop or not.
   Basically, consider "0.00%" as "unknown drop rate".


== About Fishing ==
Q: Why are some fishing sets unassigned to an area or some have multiple?
   Where is dungeon X's or residential area Y's fishing set?
A: The game files unfortunately do not assign fishing drop pools to maps.
   Therefore, the datamine makes its best guess based on the "map guides"
   in the left pane of the map. Maps like dungeons do not have these "map
   guides", so they can't be matched to any areas.


== About Rates Over 100% or Min. Quantity Over Max Quantity (3~2x) ==
Q: Some treasure chests have loot with drop rates over 100% or say
   that they drop from 3 to 2 items. What's the deal?!
A: These sorts of drops have special meaning to the game that I am not
   *fully* aware of. I'm pretty sure that, for weapons and armor at least,
   they represent "groups of classes". For example...
   * A "Leather Helmet" has a 300% 3~1x drop rate for [Archer], but there is no
     item in the group for [Sculptor]. This "Leather Helmet" likely will drop
     for both Archer, Sculptor, and NoClass (300% = 3 classes).
   * A "Dagger" has a 200% 2~1x drop rate for [Sculptor], but nothing for NoClass.
     The Dagger will, as a result, likely drop for both Sculptor and NoClass (since
     200% = 2 classes).
   * I am not sure what a rate of over 100% or 2~1x means for Option Stones or
     other non-weapon and non-armor item types.


== About ST:0 ==
Q: What the hec--
A: Don't worry about it.


== About CTRL-F ==
Q: There's so much information here and CTRL-F keeps putting me in non-useful places!
A: If you are searching for an item that is dropped or comes out of a chest,
   put curly braces around {The Item Name}. 
   For example, {Slimy Suitcase}.
   If you are searching for drops by a certain monster, search for "Monster: Monster Name".
   For example, Monster: Superslime Superstar
   If you are searching for loot box chances, search for "Item: Item Name".
   For example, Item: Lootbox Extraordinaire
   If you are searching for fishing, search for "Fishing in Zone Name".
   For example, Fishing in London


== About <X Drops> ==
Q: Why do some items have <33 Drops> in front of it?
A: Some enemies, like certain chests, rare monsters, or raid bosses, will drop multiple
   stacks of a single item when they are defeated. This says how many they drop.
   

== About Areas ==
Q: Where is (insert zone name here)?
A: It's probably unreleased content or a Chaotic Dungeon (or both).


== About Missing Items or Contributing ==
Q: I got an item from a kill that's not listed here!
A: Congratulations! Right now, I suspect that the server has special drop rates for some items
   that are not listed here, such as some chests or decorative weapons.
   I'm not taking corrections though, since this information is datamined.
